<h2>Canvas Tainting</h2>
<p>When a cross-origin image is drawn onto a <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code>, the canvas becomes "tainted" and you can no longer read its pixel data. Adding <code>crossorigin="anonymous"</code> to the image prevents tainting, provided the server sends the correct CORS headers.</p>

